I purchased this food for my recently adopted cat.  However, if you are sensitive to smells or have a cat that does not like stinky foods, DO NOT BUY THIS! I buy this food for an outdoor cat who's about 13 years old.  I'm on the third large bag of it now. Its a very nutritious food and has an appealing texture and look with what appears to be pieces of dried chicken meat mixed in with the kibble. He has been enjoying this food for months and never gets bored with it.  I'm happy knowing that he's getting good nutrition. My indoor cat, age 17, who usually doesn't care for kibble and has some health issues will also eat it, over other brands I've tried to augment her usual canned food diet.  The larger bag is a good bargain. I am careful to use bag clips and store it in a sealed container so it stays nice and fresh.

I don't know which is correct to give, a 5 star review or a 1 star one.  I chose 5 star because I buy this kibble all the time through Amazon and my cats love it.  But, I recently purchased it and it stunk to high heaven, like something was terribly wrong with it!  I called Purina and they took information from the bag to try and determine the source, use-by date etc.  I also contacted Amazon and they told me that the stinky bag I received was provided through Amazon directly, not another party, and has since been removed.  The bags now available for sale, as of the date of me writing this at least, are all from 3rd party sources and should be okay.  So, if you choose to buy it, you should be getting a quality bag and not have to worry about the stinky stuff.  Amazon also reimbursed me for the purchase.  Unfortunately I had poured the whole 16 lb. bag into my big storage container which had other good kibble in it as well.  Once I got the whiff, I ended up disposing of all the kibble in the container, including the good stuff, and thoroughly cleaning the container to be safe.  I don't know what was wrong with the stinky kibble but I sure wasn't going to let my cats taste a morsel of it!

I have been loyally feeding my cat Purina Cat Chow since adopting her 10 years ago. I have stuck with that food since she seems to enjoy it, is very vocal when her dish is empty and has had allergic reactions to other foods in the past. I received a sample of Purina ONE Tender Selects Cat Food from our veterinarian and was worried we would experience the same non-stop sneezing that we experienced the last time we switched her food. Not this time! Not only did my cat transition seamlessly and without any allergic reaction, she has been emptying her bowl. All of these years, she has been a grazer, eating here and there and leaving some food behind for later. She has been emptying her bowl and crying for more. She loved her new food so much and experienced such a seamless transition that Purina ONE Tender Selects Cat Food has become her new regular food. Although it is more expensive than Purina Cat Chow, the excitement that my cat gets and the better nutrition of this food are worth the added cost.

I started to buy this food as a cheaper alternative to feed the strays I take care of vs the exorbitantly priced stuff I buy for my indoor cats. The strays rumble with happiness as soon as they see me step out onto the porch with this food, and they eat it right up. I put out a bowl inside to see if my indoor cats would like it to, because $40-50 per 10lb bag of the food I was feeding them was becoming silly expensive. They voted with their tiny tummies, and this food won the day with a crushing victory.

I have a maine coon that weighs 15.6 lbs and he loves both the Chicken/Turkey and Salmon/Tuna. I have another domestic shorthair that I took in from being a stray when I found out she had FIV. She's gone up from a sick 6.0 lbs when I took her in to a healthy and happy 9.0 lbs eating the Chicken/Turkey and Tuna/Salmon.

And further, this actually smells like the cats enjoy it. I went vegetarian last year, and sometimes I get jealous of the cats as I'm scooping this out (I always keep 2 10lb airtight containers full of this) to feed them, and I'm almost tempted to have some.

Huge extra bonus, this is always on sale at my local supermarket, and while it is more expensive there vs. Amazon, it is still inexpensive vs other foods, and means I never have to worry about running low and having to scrounge for something else the cats will enjoy.

I do sometimes notice the food looks different from the supermarket vs. from amazon, but there seems to be no difference in smell, and the cats show no preference for amazon bought bags or store bought bags.

review_body:
Purina One SmartBlend dry cat foods are premium quality food at a moderate price.  But, check around for the best price.  Some stores in my neighborhood sell SmartBlend at very reasonable prices, yet some area pet stores sell it for much higher prices.  It pays to shop around.

Purina One Smartblend foods use premium ingredients.  My cat likes the three flavors she has tried, and is beginning to get a tad plump.  I have started limiting her to 3/4 cup a day to prevent her from OVERLY enjoying her food.

Purina uses feeding tests with cats to ensure that its formulas are healthy.  Some brands selling for TWICE the price do not do actually feed their food to cats.  They simply state on their packages that their formula meets published standards for feline nutrition.
summary: A High Quality Dry Food For Cats - Shop Around For The Best Price
